Sentencas: Atmospheric plasma spraying was employed to prepare anode, cathode, and Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 (YSZ) electrolyte to aim at reducing manufacturing cost.
Titulo: Plasma-Sprayed Y2O3-Stabilized ZrO2 Electrolyte With Improved Interlamellar Bonding for Direct Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: YSZ electrolytes were deposited on the anode at different deposition temperatures of 200 degrees C, 400 degrees C and 600 degrees C to optimize the gas tightness of plasma-sprayed YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Plasma-Sprayed Y2O3-Stabilized ZrO2 Electrolyte With Improved Interlamellar Bonding for Direct Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The influences of the deposition temperature on the microstructure and gas-tightness of plasma-sprayed YSZ electrolyte were investigated.
Titulo: Plasma-Sprayed Y2O3-Stabilized ZrO2 Electrolyte With Improved Interlamellar Bonding for Direct Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The effect of microstructure and the gas-tightness of YSZ electrolyte on the open circuit voltage and the output performance of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) were examined.
Titulo: Plasma-Sprayed Y2O3-Stabilized ZrO2 Electrolyte With Improved Interlamellar Bonding for Direct Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results showed with the increase of deposition temperature, the porosity of YSZ electrolytes almost decreased by about 80% and the microstructure of YSZ electrolytes changed from the typical lamellar structure to the continuous columnar crystal structure.
Titulo: Plasma-Sprayed Y2O3-Stabilized ZrO2 Electrolyte With Improved Interlamellar Bonding for Direct Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: At a deposition temperature of 600 degrees C the gas permeability decreased to 1.5 X 10(-7) cm 4 gf(-1) s(-1), and the highest open circuit voltage can reach 1.026 V, indicating the applicability of the as-sprayed YSZ directly to the SOFC electrolyte.
Titulo: Plasma-Sprayed Y2O3-Stabilized ZrO2 Electrolyte With Improved Interlamellar Bonding for Direct Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
